Business Brief -- Repap Enterprises Inc.:
   Pact to Sell Plant, Facilities
   For $98 Million Is Reached
Repap said that it asked lenders to its Miramichi unit to
execute a standstill agreement on interest payments for the
first quarter of 1992 until the details of the proposed sale
can be completed. At Dec. 31, 1990, Miramichi had total debt
of 604.7 million Canadian dollars (US$527.4 million). More
recent figures weren't available and Repap officials couldn't
be reached for comment.